02:44.150 --> 02:48.352
ALARIC: <i>Dear Elena,
I don't know where to start.</i>

02:51.457 --> 02:52.757
(children laughing nearby)

02:52.759 --> 02:54.392
- Hey.
- Hey.

02:54.394 --> 02:56.768
What are you doing here on your day off?

02:56.793 --> 02:58.963
Caroline told me you and
your friends lost someone.

02:58.965 --> 03:00.831
- Yeah.
- I'm happy to take

03:00.833 --> 03:03.100
the girls for the day if you need me to.

03:03.102 --> 03:04.602
I mean, that...

03:04.604 --> 03:06.737
that would be a huge help, actually.

03:06.739 --> 03:07.738
Thank you.

03:07.740 --> 03:09.540
Were you close with him?

03:09.542 --> 03:11.942
(sighs) Yeah, he was one of us.

03:11.944 --> 03:14.245
He was family.

03:14.247 --> 03:15.713
I get it.

03:15.715 --> 03:17.281
I lost my family, too.

03:17.283 --> 03:18.816
Everyone?

03:18.818 --> 03:20.084
I have a sister,

03:20.086 --> 03:22.425
but we're sort of estranged.

03:22.450 --> 03:23.815
Hmm.

03:23.840 --> 03:26.324
Yeah. Tyler's parents
died a few years ago.

03:26.326 --> 03:28.626
He was the only Lockwood left.

03:28.628 --> 03:32.196
Now it's just a whole legacy...

03:32.198 --> 03:34.999
just gone.

03:35.001 --> 03:36.834
I'm sure wherever Tyler is,

03:36.836 --> 03:38.402
he's at peace.

03:38.404 --> 03:40.705
And he knows he was loved.

03:42.775 --> 03:45.109
Look, I, uh...

03:45.111 --> 03:46.377
I really need to head out.

03:46.379 --> 03:48.312
Are you sure you don't mind?

03:48.314 --> 03:50.047
Not at all. Go.

03:50.049 --> 03:51.515
I heard there's a carnival in town.

03:51.517 --> 03:52.983
Thought it might be
nice to take the twins.

03:52.985 --> 03:54.647
(chuckling): Yeah. They would love that.

03:54.672 --> 03:55.853
LIZZIE: Seline.

03:55.878 --> 03:57.560
Hey, you two.

03:57.585 --> 03:59.018
Come play with us.

04:00.526 --> 04:02.426
Hi.

04:02.428 --> 04:04.261
- Hi.
- (Seline laughing)

04:04.263 --> 04:05.296
Who can get their shoes on first?

04:05.298 --> 04:06.430
- Me.
- I can.

04:06.432 --> 04:08.733
- I can.
- (girls laughing)

04:16.385 --> 04:18.718
That's not gonna bring him back.

04:20.279 --> 04:21.781
Tyler deserved more

04:21.807 --> 04:24.048
than to be collateral
damage in whatever game

04:24.050 --> 04:26.851
Sybil's playing with Damon.

04:26.853 --> 04:29.387
Yeah. I can't even remember
our last conversation.

04:29.389 --> 04:31.889
We haven't talked in months.

04:31.891 --> 04:34.392
We've both been so busy.

04:34.394 --> 04:36.026
After everything we went through,

04:36.028 --> 04:39.864
I guess I just always assumed
that he would be there.

04:41.234 --> 04:43.667
I'm at a loss with Damon.

04:43.669 --> 04:46.937
I don't know what to do with him anymore.

04:46.939 --> 04:51.470
Maybe the best thing to
do is just to mourn Tyler

04:51.495 --> 04:52.710
with your friends.

04:52.712 --> 04:55.813
We all owe him that.

04:58.651 --> 05:00.818
(sighs)

05:07.960 --> 05:09.894
Oh, don't mind me, luv.

05:12.131 --> 05:14.799
Something wrong?

05:14.801 --> 05:16.901
I'm fine.

05:16.903 --> 05:18.135
Wow.

05:18.137 --> 05:20.771
So Damon murders Tyler Lockwood,

05:20.773 --> 05:23.040
in cold blood, and you're fine with it.

05:23.042 --> 05:25.176
I didn't mean to eavesdrop on your call,

05:25.178 --> 05:27.557
but that seems like a
decidedly not fine situation,

05:27.582 --> 05:28.712
at least to me.

05:28.714 --> 05:31.515
But that grief that you're
trying damn hard to hide

05:31.517 --> 05:35.052
is giving you this beautiful glow.

05:37.557 --> 05:39.690
Set me free, Bonnie.

05:39.692 --> 05:41.625
Set us both free.

05:41.627 --> 05:44.062
I'll take you on a proper date.

05:44.087 --> 05:45.396
Anywhere you'd like.

05:45.398 --> 05:47.031
Paris...

05:47.033 --> 05:50.134
You can fix everything
that's broken inside of me.

05:50.136 --> 05:52.736
You can fix us.

05:56.709 --> 05:59.777
Your wrists look a little raw.

06:03.082 --> 06:05.749
I'll help you out.

06:08.321 --> 06:11.255
Ah.

06:12.992 --> 06:15.759
(groans)

06:17.129 --> 06:18.629
(sighs)

06:18.631 --> 06:19.997
Bonnie Bennett,

06:19.999 --> 06:22.466
you are my saving grace.

06:28.808 --> 06:31.709
You spelled the cabin?

06:31.711 --> 06:33.410
You've been keeping a secret from me.

06:33.412 --> 06:34.845
Are you a witch again?

06:34.847 --> 06:36.447
I'm actually not.

06:36.449 --> 06:38.048
Still don't have my magic,

06:38.050 --> 06:40.084
but doesn't mean I can't
use a magical object.

06:40.086 --> 06:42.853
This is a dark object
on loan from the Armory.

06:42.855 --> 06:45.089
It's called a "flame of imprisonment."

06:45.091 --> 06:46.490
Well, aren't you fancy?

06:46.492 --> 06:48.431
It traps supernatural beings

06:48.456 --> 06:49.907
in the space where it burns.

06:49.932 --> 06:51.795
I can come and go because
I'm the one who lit it.

06:51.797 --> 06:54.331
And I'm the only one who can put it out.

06:54.333 --> 06:57.568
And I won't... unless you turn

06:57.570 --> 06:59.036
your humanity back on.

06:59.038 --> 07:01.372
Why are you suddenly taking this stand?

07:01.374 --> 07:03.574
Because Tyler Lockwood is dead.

07:03.576 --> 07:06.110
And I'm not gonna lose you, too.

07:10.216 --> 07:12.349
(footsteps approaching)

07:13.786 --> 07:15.819
What are you doing?

07:19.525 --> 07:21.158
(groans)

07:22.228 --> 07:23.661
Savasana.

07:23.663 --> 07:25.396
It's restorative.

07:25.398 --> 07:27.181
It promotes physical

07:27.206 --> 07:29.633
and emotional well-being.

07:29.635 --> 07:30.701
(fork tines humming)

07:30.703 --> 07:32.536
(groans)

07:34.640 --> 07:37.308
So not Zen.

07:37.310 --> 07:39.176
- That's for Tyler.
- To be fair,

07:39.178 --> 07:41.345
that was more Damon than it was me.

07:41.347 --> 07:43.547
I simply suggested that
he do whatever he could

07:43.549 --> 07:45.249
to sever his remaining ties.

07:45.251 --> 07:47.086
(tines humming)

07:47.111 --> 07:49.153
Georgie, where is she?

07:51.157 --> 07:53.524
I already have another cell ready.

07:53.526 --> 07:55.593
Labeled Siren Number Two.

07:57.296 --> 07:59.830
Oh, wait, that's right,
I can't see anything.

07:59.832 --> 08:02.255
My psychic abilities have
been neutralized.

08:02.280 --> 08:04.668
(tines humming)

08:04.670 --> 08:07.071
I set up an intercom system here.

08:07.073 --> 08:10.374
So this noise and pain will haunt you

08:10.376 --> 08:13.010
from now on, 24/7.

08:13.012 --> 08:16.413
Welcome to your psychic hell.

08:16.415 --> 08:19.583
(tines ringing)

08:19.585 --> 08:21.685
(switch clicks)

08:21.687 --> 08:23.053
(microphone feedback whines)

08:23.055 --> 08:24.655
- Intercom's up and running.
- Oh, good.

08:24.680 --> 08:26.457
Listen, I need you to test
the frequency levels

08:26.459 --> 08:27.758
every hour on the hour.

08:27.760 --> 08:28.750
It's incredibly important.

08:28.774 --> 08:30.101
Can I ask why?

08:30.126 --> 08:32.039
Well, because I believe
the vibrational motion

08:32.063 --> 08:34.431
had something to do with the
formation of the tunnels.

08:34.433 --> 08:35.933
That makes almost no sense.

08:35.934 --> 08:37.267
Okay, how about because I said so?

08:37.269 --> 08:40.494
Also, I got a really odd text
from Georgie last night,

08:40.519 --> 08:42.072
saying she had to leave town suddenly.

08:42.073 --> 08:43.573
She wouldn't ditch work.

08:43.576 --> 08:45.042
- Not while we're in the middle
of all this. - Agreed.

08:45.044 --> 08:46.744
Which is why I need you
to do some digging.

08:46.746 --> 08:48.579
Call her roommate, find out what's up.

08:48.604 --> 08:49.640
We need to find her right away.

08:49.642 --> 08:51.115
What about the frequency research?

08:51.117 --> 08:52.583
Multi-task.

08:52.585 --> 08:54.618
Test the frequency, look for Georgie.

08:54.620 --> 08:57.221
Call me if anything strange happens.

09:01.193 --> 09:04.428
♪ ♪

09:24.502 --> 09:26.368
DAMON: I was wondering when you guys

09:26.370 --> 09:28.470
were gonna show up.

09:28.472 --> 09:30.705
Body's probably starting
to smell a little bit.

09:30.730 --> 09:32.603
Tried to keep it as intact as I could.

09:32.628 --> 09:34.943
But I got to admit,
I got a little carried away

09:34.968 --> 09:38.145
about the whole ripping
the throat out thing.

09:38.147 --> 09:39.792
My apologies to Donovan.

09:39.817 --> 09:42.351
I'm sure you cleaned him up real nice.

09:45.325 --> 09:46.989
What are you gonna do with that?

09:46.991 --> 09:48.223
Stake me?

09:48.225 --> 09:49.858
Go ahead, try it.

09:49.860 --> 09:51.627
But first...

09:52.196 --> 09:54.396
Take your pick.

09:54.398 --> 09:57.332
'Cause I'm gonna bury every one of you.

10:02.392 --> 10:03.958
DAMON: Easy.

10:03.960 --> 10:05.593
Underestimating me

10:05.595 --> 10:07.095
is what got Tyler killed.

10:10.100 --> 10:11.466
Matt Donovan.

10:11.468 --> 10:13.101
The only living boy in Mystic Falls.

10:13.103 --> 10:15.907
You know, it's shocking you
managed to stay human this long.

10:15.939 --> 10:17.093
Maybe I should fix that.

10:17.118 --> 10:18.173
STEFAN: Is that why
you came home, Damon?

10:18.175 --> 10:19.474
To make empty threats?

10:19.476 --> 10:20.508
Not empty, brother.

10:20.510 --> 10:22.177
(grunts)

10:22.179 --> 10:24.078
Don't move or I'll snap his neck.

10:24.080 --> 10:26.481
Give Matt here a
non-transferrable invitation

10:26.483 --> 10:28.383
to our supernatural breakfast club.

10:28.385 --> 10:31.085
Damon, enough.

10:31.087 --> 10:32.921
Sweet Caroline. How many

10:32.923 --> 10:35.690
innocent people did you kill on
your no humanity bender, hmm?

10:35.692 --> 10:38.126
Doesn't matter what you say or don't.

10:38.128 --> 10:40.028
The devil knows what you did.

10:40.030 --> 10:41.830
What's happened to you?

10:42.999 --> 10:45.066
What's so surprising about this?

10:45.068 --> 10:46.601
I'm who I've always been.

10:46.603 --> 10:48.636
No. No, you're different.

10:48.661 --> 10:52.969
(chuckles) Professor Ric
Saltzman, everyone.

10:52.994 --> 10:54.309
Certified genius.

10:54.311 --> 10:56.344
Knows you better than you know yourself.

10:56.346 --> 10:58.513
CAROLINE: Damon, just go.

10:58.515 --> 11:00.548
Nobody wants you here.

11:05.689 --> 11:07.388
You all despise me, right?

11:07.390 --> 11:08.990
Just so we're clear, hmm?

11:08.992 --> 11:11.159
I killed Tyler, you hate my guts,

11:11.161 --> 11:13.647
our ties are severed, huh? Great.

11:13.649 --> 11:15.779
If you thought there was
any remaining opportunity

11:15.804 --> 11:20.301
to rescue me, let this prove you wrong.

11:20.303 --> 11:23.505
(panting)

11:25.375 --> 11:27.141
CAROLINE: <i>It was awful.</i>

11:27.143 --> 11:29.344
Like Damon's desperate
for us all to hate him.

11:29.346 --> 11:30.845
Sorry I wasn't there.

11:30.847 --> 11:33.114
I want to be there.
I just... I can't leave.

11:33.116 --> 11:35.342
Please tell me it's going
better than it did yesterday.

11:35.367 --> 11:37.719
It's worse, if that's even possible.

11:37.721 --> 11:40.321
Drying him out didn't work.
Starving him didn't work.

11:40.323 --> 11:43.273
I played the guitar.
I told him our history.

11:43.298 --> 11:44.993
It's like talking to a brick wall.

11:44.995 --> 11:47.328
What did it for you, when you
had your humanity off?

11:47.330 --> 11:49.097
What made you break free?

11:49.099 --> 11:53.134
(sighs) I had to face my biggest fear.

11:53.136 --> 11:55.470
That I wasn't worth loving anymore.

11:55.472 --> 11:59.474
And that my mom would be ashamed of me.

11:59.476 --> 12:02.477
I had to be reminded how
much she loved me,

12:02.479 --> 12:07.415
and then I had to
want to live up to that.

12:08.285 --> 12:09.918
Is that helpful?

12:09.920 --> 12:12.086
Yeah.

12:12.088 --> 12:13.555
It is.

12:13.557 --> 12:15.356
Keep me posted.

12:15.358 --> 12:16.865
And don't worry about not being here.

12:16.890 --> 12:19.294
We'll give Tyler a proper
good-bye when this is all over.

12:19.296 --> 12:21.896
- Yeah, when will that be?
- Soon.

12:21.898 --> 12:23.131
I hope.

12:23.133 --> 12:25.233
I hope so, too.

12:25.235 --> 12:26.701
(phone beeps)

12:26.703 --> 12:28.469
(sighs)

12:28.471 --> 12:30.371
ENZO: Dead friend problems?

12:30.373 --> 12:33.374
My heart bleeds for you.

12:33.376 --> 12:35.510
All this trauma.

12:35.512 --> 12:37.845
The burden of always
having to protect everyone.

12:37.847 --> 12:40.148
Why don't you just take me
off your plate, hmm?

12:40.150 --> 12:43.585
Why don't you just turn
your humanity back on?

12:43.587 --> 12:47.322
(sighs) Can't we both agree that
my humanity was a hindrance?

12:47.324 --> 12:49.624
I was angry, depressed.

12:49.626 --> 12:51.926
A-A tragic poet full of darkness.

12:51.928 --> 12:53.895
(sighs)

12:53.897 --> 12:55.797
Where's the fun in reverting back

12:55.799 --> 12:58.866
to an inferior version of myself?

13:00.136 --> 13:03.371
You were a lot of amazing things, too.

13:03.373 --> 13:05.974
You were loyal, creative,

13:05.976 --> 13:08.710
and wildly romantic.

13:08.712 --> 13:10.712
Mmm.

13:10.714 --> 13:13.514
Well, you know, even if I did turn it on,

13:13.516 --> 13:14.849
it's too late for you.

13:14.851 --> 13:17.185
You missed Tyler's funeral.

13:17.187 --> 13:18.987
Abandoning your friends
in their time of need.

13:18.989 --> 13:21.322
That, my dear, is cold.

13:23.693 --> 13:25.426
I'll be back.

13:28.331 --> 13:31.065
I'll still be here.

13:31.067 --> 13:33.601
Thanks to you.

13:36.606 --> 13:39.240
Remember, it's not Damon.

13:39.242 --> 13:41.576
This is Damon under the
control of a she-devil.

13:41.578 --> 13:43.945
And we have to find a way to
break her control. And we will.

13:43.947 --> 13:45.348
I've got my interns working on it.

13:45.373 --> 13:47.882
And, in the meantime,
what, let him run wild

13:47.884 --> 13:49.550
and kill another one of our friends?

13:49.552 --> 13:50.885
I am trying to prevent that, you know.

13:50.887 --> 13:53.154
Look, even if we break Sybil's hold,

13:53.156 --> 13:55.623
once Damon realizes what he's done,

13:55.625 --> 13:58.993
what Elena will think of him,
he may not recover.

13:58.995 --> 14:01.162
What are you suggesting?

14:01.164 --> 14:04.899
While we figure out how to
save Damon from the sirens,

14:04.901 --> 14:06.234
we have to figure out

14:06.236 --> 14:08.036
how to save him from himself.

14:08.038 --> 14:10.638
We have to put him down.

14:11.374 --> 14:13.041
For how long?

14:13.043 --> 14:14.842
As long as we need to.

14:14.844 --> 14:16.144
You sure?

14:17.414 --> 14:19.013
It's for his own good.

14:19.015 --> 14:22.350
And it's the only way that
we can protect ourselves.

14:29.125 --> 14:31.101
Well, this is a surprise.

14:31.126 --> 14:32.570
To be clear, we're not friends,

14:32.595 --> 14:34.362
and I'm not here to set you free.

14:34.364 --> 14:36.964
In fact, I never want to see you again.

14:36.966 --> 14:40.535
- Why are you here then?
- Because I want answers.

14:40.537 --> 14:43.337
I stole that hunk of junk
from Donovan's mystery dad.

14:43.339 --> 14:44.839
Burned all my bridges.

14:44.841 --> 14:46.974
Made everybody hate me. I'm guessing

14:46.976 --> 14:49.177
it's because you're still in my head.

14:49.179 --> 14:50.445
And what makes you think that?

14:50.447 --> 14:51.913
Because none of it's for me.

14:51.915 --> 14:54.282
I can't quite understand
why I have free will

14:54.284 --> 14:55.516
and yet I'm still

14:55.518 --> 14:57.552
your errand boy. I do things

14:57.554 --> 15:01.055
to make you happy, and I don't know why.

15:01.057 --> 15:03.458
Sounds like you have regrets.

15:03.460 --> 15:06.427
Regret implies that you're
not a loyal servant.

15:06.429 --> 15:08.996
What are you talking about?
I killed Tyler Lockwood.

15:08.998 --> 15:11.899
- Of course I'm loyal.
- No, you're upset

15:11.901 --> 15:13.412
because you upset your friends.

15:13.437 --> 15:15.536
My friends don't care about me anymore.

15:15.538 --> 15:17.405
But you killed someone
that they do care about.

15:17.407 --> 15:19.173
That must've made them feel something.

15:19.175 --> 15:21.642
Sure looks like it made
you feel something.

15:21.644 --> 15:23.845
Here you are, troubled, hostile.

15:23.847 --> 15:25.446
You know what that tells me?

15:25.448 --> 15:26.981
That you're not completely mine.

15:26.983 --> 15:28.683
That the cold, dark heart

15:28.685 --> 15:32.086
of Damon Salvatore felt a flash of pain

15:32.088 --> 15:34.622
when he took Tyler Lockwood's life away.

15:34.624 --> 15:36.290
It made you feel,

15:36.292 --> 15:38.126
and it felt bad.

15:38.151 --> 15:39.942
I don't feel anything anymore.

15:39.944 --> 15:40.995
Wrong.

15:40.997 --> 15:42.797
It's written all over your face.

15:42.799 --> 15:45.767
Your humanity is riding
that dimmer switch,

15:45.769 --> 15:47.902
and right now it is pushing itself up.

15:47.904 --> 15:49.670
And it feels terrible, doesn't it?

15:49.672 --> 15:51.038
- Shut up.
- Dimmer goes up,

15:51.040 --> 15:52.406
and you'll get your feelings back.

15:52.408 --> 15:54.509
Maybe your brother will love you again.

15:54.511 --> 15:57.044
But, boy, will it feel awful.

15:57.046 --> 15:59.781
And Elena's reaction to
everything you've done,

15:59.783 --> 16:01.382
let's not even think about that.

16:01.384 --> 16:03.651
Stop talking.

16:03.653 --> 16:06.463
Dimmer that switch back down,

16:06.488 --> 16:08.790
and all these bad feelings
and all this confusion,

16:08.792 --> 16:10.858
it'll all disappear.

16:10.860 --> 16:14.061
Me? I prefer Option B.

16:14.063 --> 16:17.465
- The dimmer down. Total abandonment.
- (groans)

16:18.268 --> 16:19.433
I said shut up.

16:19.435 --> 16:22.403
Shut up!

16:22.405 --> 16:25.573
What do you want from me?

16:25.575 --> 16:27.842
I want you, Damon.

16:27.844 --> 16:29.744
All of you.

16:29.746 --> 16:32.280
I can rewrite your subconscious,
but that will only get me

16:32.282 --> 16:33.781
so far.

16:33.783 --> 16:35.116
I'm not going to have you

16:35.118 --> 16:36.417
the way that I want you

16:36.419 --> 16:37.718
while you still have

16:37.720 --> 16:40.421
these emotional ties to your past.

16:47.463 --> 16:50.464
Go see your brother.

16:50.466 --> 16:54.435
Let him guide that dimmer switch
up until you feel everything.

16:54.437 --> 16:57.672
If that's how you want to live
your life, go ahead... live it.

16:57.674 --> 17:02.118
Maybe you'll find some
small pockets of happiness

17:02.143 --> 17:05.055
before death delivers you to Cade.

17:27.211 --> 17:30.379
Hey, uh, somebody just
dropped this off for you.

17:30.381 --> 17:32.147
Said he was from the Armory?

17:32.149 --> 17:34.269
Yeah. Just, uh, put it down.
I'll go through it later.

17:38.055 --> 17:41.890
Box everything up. Room by room.

17:43.153 --> 17:46.528
Uh, Matt, you know, we
can do this tomorrow.

17:46.530 --> 17:48.230
Or the day after, if you need time.

17:48.232 --> 17:49.731
No, it's fine.

17:49.733 --> 17:53.035
I'm an expert at dealing
with loss, you know?

17:53.037 --> 17:55.003
Started at a young age.

17:55.005 --> 17:56.438
(sighs)

17:56.440 --> 17:59.508
Yeah, I guess I deserve that.

18:00.878 --> 18:04.413
You do and you don't.

18:04.415 --> 18:06.982
I'm sorry. It's just...

18:06.984 --> 18:09.618
Tyler and this place

18:09.620 --> 18:13.922
and the fact that I have
vampire blood in my system.

18:13.924 --> 18:17.526
And if I die in the next 24 hours,
I'm gonna become one.

18:18.395 --> 18:20.596
How did it come to this?

18:20.598 --> 18:21.830
How did all this happen?

18:21.832 --> 18:23.532
"All this"?

18:24.869 --> 18:27.603
What do you mean? Like vampires

18:27.605 --> 18:29.738
and vervain and...

18:29.740 --> 18:30.739
(shuddering breath)

18:30.741 --> 18:33.175
...and death?

18:33.177 --> 18:35.177
This was my life.

18:35.179 --> 18:36.578
This is what I dealt with.

18:36.580 --> 18:39.615
Alone. For a long time.

18:39.617 --> 18:42.551
This is what I wanted to escape.

18:42.553 --> 18:45.287
So, forgive me

18:45.289 --> 18:48.357
if I'm not in the mood to
give you a history lesson.

18:58.636 --> 19:01.303
(sighs)

19:12.683 --> 19:14.616
TYLER: <i>Matt, if you got this,</i>

19:14.618 --> 19:17.853
<i>it means I'm dead, which sucks.</i>

19:17.855 --> 19:22.591
<i>It also means I need your
help finding someone.</i>

19:34.772 --> 19:36.939
Thought you were gone for the day.

19:36.941 --> 19:38.473
Hey, take a look at this, will you?

19:38.475 --> 19:40.542
Yeah.

19:40.544 --> 19:42.978
So, the distance between
Mystic Falls and the Armory

19:42.980 --> 19:44.938
is roughly 35 miles.

19:44.963 --> 19:46.415
Winding roads, hill country.

19:46.417 --> 19:47.749
But I was able to walk the distance

19:47.751 --> 19:49.284
of that tunnel in just a few hours.

19:49.286 --> 19:52.521
Which would make it, what, seven miles?

19:52.523 --> 19:54.456
The tunnel must cut directly
under the mountains.

19:54.458 --> 19:56.959
Right. But the walls are old.

19:56.961 --> 19:58.226
Centuries, at least.

19:58.228 --> 19:59.728
So who the hell built them?

19:59.730 --> 20:00.829
And why?

20:00.831 --> 20:01.997
Hmm.

20:01.999 --> 20:03.565
You want me to get into it?

20:03.567 --> 20:06.468
No. No, I'll figure it out.

20:06.470 --> 20:09.504
- So what's the latest on Georgie?
- I called her roommate.

20:09.506 --> 20:11.473
She said all of Georgie's
stuff is still in her room.

20:11.475 --> 20:13.075
If she left, she didn't
take anything with her.

20:13.077 --> 20:14.476
Okay, I need you to call the police

20:14.478 --> 20:15.777
and file a missing persons report.

20:15.779 --> 20:16.912
Seriously?

20:16.914 --> 20:18.146
It's just a precaution.

20:18.148 --> 20:19.815
How's the frequency research coming?

20:19.817 --> 20:21.850
You keep acting like I'm
doing something scientific.

20:21.852 --> 20:23.482
I'm literally banging a fork.

20:23.507 --> 20:25.320
It's ridiculous, and I've
learned nothing.

20:25.322 --> 20:27.856
You ever gonna tell me
what this is all about?

20:28.726 --> 20:31.259
One day.

20:33.230 --> 20:34.863
(carnival music playing)

20:34.865 --> 20:36.465
(indistinct chatter, laughter)

20:40.004 --> 20:41.470
(clinking)

20:41.472 --> 20:43.638
Good try.

20:43.640 --> 20:45.774
(chuckling): Almost.

20:45.776 --> 20:47.743
This is too hard.

20:47.745 --> 20:49.077
Oh.

20:49.079 --> 20:52.681
(humming softly)

20:54.785 --> 20:56.284
Why don't you give the girls

20:56.286 --> 20:58.954
- a goldfish for their efforts?
- (gasps, squeals)

20:58.956 --> 21:02.391
We'll take that one.

21:03.694 --> 21:06.695
Is he sick?

21:06.697 --> 21:08.597
Aw, I think he might be dead.

21:08.599 --> 21:10.399
But that's okay. Tell you what,

21:10.401 --> 21:12.834
we'll take him home and
give him a proper burial.

21:12.836 --> 21:14.736
- Okay.
- Okay?

21:17.975 --> 21:20.008
(footsteps approaching)

21:20.010 --> 21:21.910
CAROLINE: I swear,

21:21.912 --> 21:24.713
if Seline wasn't so good with
the girls, I would hate her.

21:24.715 --> 21:27.516
She's too perfect to be a real person.

21:27.518 --> 21:29.184
- Who's that for?
- Got a text from Damon

21:29.186 --> 21:30.144
a little while ago.

21:30.169 --> 21:31.887
He wants to meet up at the carnival.

21:31.889 --> 21:33.855
- Why the carnival?
- I don't know.

21:33.880 --> 21:35.816
But this is my only chance,
I don't know if I'll get another

21:35.840 --> 21:36.625
so I have to take it.

21:36.627 --> 21:38.191
- Are you gonna need some help?
- No.

21:38.216 --> 21:40.362
I'm not putting you in any
more danger, Caroline.

21:40.364 --> 21:43.365
Two vampires are better
than one, it's basic math.

21:43.367 --> 21:46.334
I have to do this on my own.

21:47.438 --> 21:49.604
It's the right thing.

21:49.606 --> 21:51.740
Okay? You know it is.

21:53.043 --> 21:56.878
He might not forgive me after this.

21:58.246 --> 22:01.950
And I might lose him forever.

22:01.952 --> 22:04.386
You already lost him.

22:11.462 --> 22:13.662
(jazz music plays)

22:19.071 --> 22:21.303
Happy New Year's, luv.

22:21.305 --> 22:22.938
Come on, dance with me.

22:22.940 --> 22:24.239
Hmm? Like we used to.

22:24.241 --> 22:26.341
Oh, I remember now, all the lights,

22:26.343 --> 22:28.076
the music, mmm.

22:28.078 --> 22:29.778
Screw you.

22:30.423 --> 22:32.557
You didn't buy it? Not just a little?

22:32.582 --> 22:34.449
I'm glad you found a new
way to amuse yourself.

22:34.451 --> 22:35.584
Yeah, sorry. Can't help it.

22:35.586 --> 22:39.154
Romance... the slow burn of it all.

22:39.156 --> 22:40.451
Oh, it was so

22:40.476 --> 22:42.791
unbelievably saccharine.

22:42.793 --> 22:44.757
And for what? I kept you safe

22:44.782 --> 22:47.449
for three years and then
you tried to kill me.

22:48.398 --> 22:50.565
It looks like

22:50.567 --> 22:52.400
you might be trying that again?

22:52.402 --> 22:54.269
I'm gonna get through to you.

22:54.271 --> 22:56.004
I'm gonna use your darkest fears

22:56.006 --> 22:57.672
to pull you out of this.

22:57.674 --> 23:00.108
Okay, well, I'm a complicated person.

23:00.110 --> 23:02.177
In my 140 years on this Earth,

23:02.179 --> 23:04.012
- no one's figured me out.
- Oh, well.

23:04.014 --> 23:05.580
Guess I'll die trying.

23:05.582 --> 23:06.748
(gas splashing)

23:06.750 --> 23:09.985
(laughing): Oh.

23:09.987 --> 23:12.355
You think I'm afraid of fire

23:12.380 --> 23:15.223
because Damon left me in a fire.

23:15.225 --> 23:17.259
(chuckling): Nice try.

23:17.261 --> 23:18.960
But no.

23:20.631 --> 23:22.898
You're afraid of people leaving.

23:22.900 --> 23:24.166
Period.

23:24.168 --> 23:26.735
You're afraid of being abandoned.

23:26.737 --> 23:29.771
The one thing that happens
to you again and again.

23:29.773 --> 23:33.708
- Everyone leaves, no one stays.
- Hmm.

23:33.710 --> 23:35.810
Well, that ends now.

23:35.812 --> 23:38.680
'Cause I'm not going anywhere.

23:38.682 --> 23:40.015
Yeah, well...

23:40.017 --> 23:42.584
This is a bit extreme, don't you think?

23:42.586 --> 23:46.721
Well, desperate times call
for desperate measures.

23:46.723 --> 23:49.691
I'm not leaving until you
turn your humanity back on.

23:49.693 --> 23:52.561
I'd rather burn alive than abandon you.

24:06.276 --> 24:08.476
(indistinct crowd chatter)

24:16.386 --> 24:17.686
Hey, what's going on?

24:17.688 --> 24:20.589
Gas leak, we're being evacuated.

24:26.997 --> 24:29.297
Hello, brother.

24:32.436 --> 24:34.569
Stefan.

24:34.571 --> 24:36.671
I need your help.

24:43.670 --> 24:45.903
I got to say, I'm surprised.

24:45.905 --> 24:46.873
Last time I saw you,

24:46.898 --> 24:48.906
you seemed pretty
hell-bent on severing ties.

24:48.931 --> 24:51.528
Yeah, in hindsight, that might
have been a bit dramatic.

24:51.530 --> 24:53.444
Well, it's a little late to take it back.

24:53.446 --> 24:54.779
Even if Sybil made you do it.

24:54.804 --> 24:57.381
Yeah, see, this is where it gets tricky.

24:57.383 --> 24:59.717
I want to serve her,
Stefan, I mean, I have to.

24:59.719 --> 25:01.112
And serving her keeps me away

25:01.137 --> 25:02.753
from the big bad devil himself.

25:02.755 --> 25:03.988
And I want to stay away from hell

25:03.990 --> 25:05.556
as long as humanly possible.

25:05.558 --> 25:07.899
- By turning off your humanity?
- There are worse fates.

25:07.924 --> 25:08.859
You know I can help you.

25:08.861 --> 25:11.128
If you let me.

25:12.465 --> 25:14.899
You're gonna make me turn it back on.

25:14.901 --> 25:16.088
No.

25:16.113 --> 25:18.414
No, I-I-I-I-I don't want
to do that, Stefan.

25:18.439 --> 25:19.437
You have to.

25:19.439 --> 25:21.105
You can't keep doing what you're doing.

25:21.107 --> 25:23.174
Why not? Isn't this easier?

25:23.176 --> 25:25.176
There are no amends to be made, Stefan.

25:25.178 --> 25:27.442
I can't munch on bunnies and save people,

25:27.467 --> 25:29.146
and work my way back to peace.

25:30.362 --> 25:31.962
I'm hell-bound.

25:31.964 --> 25:33.597
So, why? Tell me.

25:33.599 --> 25:36.467
Knowing what I know, why would
I ever want to feel again?

25:36.469 --> 25:38.235
Because if we can't feel,

25:38.237 --> 25:40.771
then what's the point
of being alive, huh?

25:43.423 --> 25:45.223
Exactly, brother.

25:48.514 --> 25:50.714
- What's the point?
- No.

25:50.716 --> 25:52.316
I'm not buying it.

25:52.318 --> 25:55.252
I can see your humanity trying
to break through, Damon.

25:55.254 --> 25:56.520
Come home with me.

25:56.522 --> 25:58.522
I can help you be happy again.

25:58.524 --> 25:59.756
How?

25:59.758 --> 26:02.025
It'll take time and work.

26:02.027 --> 26:04.294
But I'll be there for you.

26:05.865 --> 26:08.966
I-I... I can't, Stefan.

26:08.968 --> 26:11.001
- I ruined everything.
- Hey.

26:11.003 --> 26:13.270
I am your brother,

26:13.272 --> 26:15.706
and I love you.

26:15.708 --> 26:18.709
Just come home with me.

26:19.945 --> 26:23.247
No... I can't.

26:26.919 --> 26:28.952
(grunting)

26:28.954 --> 26:31.421
Is that how you help me? Vervain?

26:31.423 --> 26:33.357
I don't have any choice, you don't
know what you're doing.

26:33.359 --> 26:35.025
I know exactly what I'm doing, brother.

26:35.027 --> 26:36.560
Humanity's gone dark.

26:36.562 --> 26:38.862
Anything goes now.

26:54.013 --> 26:56.413
(exhales)

26:56.415 --> 26:58.649
ENZO: Congratulations, you nailed it.

26:58.651 --> 27:00.918
Fear of abandonment, a textbook case.

27:00.920 --> 27:03.554
- Now can we end this?
- I'm not leaving you.

27:03.556 --> 27:05.055
I really hope you leave at some point.

27:05.057 --> 27:06.690
I mean, this cabin's
gonna run out of food.

27:06.692 --> 27:08.225
I really question UberEat"

27:08.227 --> 27:09.660
ability to locate this address.

27:09.662 --> 27:12.062
(coughing): I'm not leaving you.

27:12.064 --> 27:13.397
- I know. I get it.
- No.

27:13.399 --> 27:14.865
(coughing)

27:14.867 --> 27:17.901
Smoke doesn't feel good
in the lungs, does it?

27:17.903 --> 27:19.536
(sniffs)

27:19.538 --> 27:21.805
I'm not leaving you.

27:21.807 --> 27:23.173
And I still don't care.

27:23.175 --> 27:25.375
Now you're just being stupid.

27:32.151 --> 27:33.984
I'm not leaving you.

27:35.287 --> 27:38.488
Any other last words?

27:41.293 --> 27:42.826
(groans)

27:42.828 --> 27:45.095
I'm...

27:45.097 --> 27:47.965
not...

27:47.967 --> 27:50.300
leaving...

27:50.302 --> 27:52.336
...you.

27:52.338 --> 27:54.171
You're as good as dead.

27:54.173 --> 27:55.839
(groaning)

27:55.841 --> 27:57.774
(fire roaring)

27:57.776 --> 27:59.710
I'm not... (groans)

28:10.022 --> 28:12.155
(fire roaring, glass shattering)

28:19.865 --> 28:21.898
Bonnie.

28:21.900 --> 28:24.835
Bonnie, wake up.

28:43.122 --> 28:46.723
Are we gonna bury the fish?

28:46.725 --> 28:48.892
Yes, but in our own way.

28:48.894 --> 28:52.663
You see, we are made up of two parts.

28:52.665 --> 28:55.666
Our body and our soul.

28:55.668 --> 29:00.214
See, some people are very special.

29:00.239 --> 29:01.905
And when they die,

29:01.907 --> 29:04.474
a man named Cade

29:04.476 --> 29:06.476
comes to take their soul away.

29:06.478 --> 29:08.945
- Does he take the body, too?
- No.

29:08.947 --> 29:11.948
But that doesn't mean the
bodies aren't special, too.

29:11.950 --> 29:14.184
They need to be treated with dignity

29:14.186 --> 29:16.953
to find peace in death.

29:16.955 --> 29:19.222
And Cade respects that.

29:19.224 --> 29:22.592
He appreciates the effort.

29:24.697 --> 29:26.163
Let's show him what we did.

29:26.165 --> 29:27.998
- How?
- We can call him.

29:28.000 --> 29:30.430
But I need you to hold my hand, okay?

29:33.938 --> 29:36.506
(Seline humming)

29:40.612 --> 29:42.799
Did we hurt you?

29:42.824 --> 29:45.382
Oh, not at all, you were perfect.

29:45.384 --> 29:48.418
You took just the right amount of magic.

29:48.420 --> 29:52.689
Now... I need you to say the special word.

29:52.691 --> 29:54.524
LIZZE AND JOSIE: <i>Incendia.</i>

29:55.627 --> 29:57.828
(gasps)

29:58.981 --> 30:00.781
Excellent job, girls.

30:02.234 --> 30:05.369
- I think you're ready.
- For what?

30:05.371 --> 30:08.338
It's a surprise.

30:20.119 --> 30:22.185
(fire crackling)

30:22.187 --> 30:24.354
(Enzo coughing)

30:26.692 --> 30:27.858
Enzo!

30:28.827 --> 30:31.161
(coughs)

30:31.163 --> 30:33.130
You came back to me.

30:33.132 --> 30:34.598
ENZO: Of course I did.

30:34.600 --> 30:37.334
Someone had to save you. (coughing)

30:37.336 --> 30:41.338
- No... No!
- Bonnie.

30:42.474 --> 30:43.940
My time.

30:49.648 --> 30:53.850
You loved me more than anyone.

30:57.923 --> 30:59.356
That's enough.

31:00.526 --> 31:02.492
(coughing)

31:05.664 --> 31:07.964
No! I'm not leaving you.

31:10.669 --> 31:14.237
(groans)

31:14.239 --> 31:15.672
Bonnie!

31:17.342 --> 31:18.742
I'm sorry. Sorry.

31:18.744 --> 31:20.644
- It's okay. (groans)
- I'm so sorry.

31:20.646 --> 31:22.212
(groans)

31:22.214 --> 31:24.548
It's okay. It's okay. We're okay.

31:24.550 --> 31:27.184
(panting)

31:27.186 --> 31:29.252
I almost killed you.

31:29.254 --> 31:30.487
I'm still here.

31:31.323 --> 31:33.623
Look at me.

31:33.625 --> 31:36.793
(chuckles) You're okay now.

31:36.795 --> 31:39.095
You're okay.

31:39.097 --> 31:42.232
And you're stuck with me forever.

31:46.305 --> 31:49.406
'Cause I'm never leaving.

31:49.408 --> 31:51.708
♪ ♪

32:11.759 --> 32:13.692
(chains rattling)

32:13.694 --> 32:16.294
♪ ♪

32:27.608 --> 32:29.641
(exhales)

32:29.643 --> 32:32.611
I'm sorry.

32:32.613 --> 32:35.347
(lid creaking)

32:38.786 --> 32:40.919
(sighs)

32:50.464 --> 32:52.831
What's all this?

32:52.833 --> 32:54.800
You don't want to know.

32:54.802 --> 32:56.635
Try me.

32:56.637 --> 32:59.671
Tyler was helping this girl
named Virginia St. John

32:59.673 --> 33:02.874
locate the sirens who escaped the vault.

33:02.876 --> 33:06.001
Well, she had all this
research and letters and stuff

33:06.026 --> 33:08.346
from her great-grandfather, Dalton.

33:08.348 --> 33:11.603
He released one of the sirens in 1883.

33:11.628 --> 33:14.686
Then Virginia died and she
willed all this to Tyler.

33:14.688 --> 33:16.254
Then he died.

33:16.256 --> 33:18.256
- And now...
- And he wants

33:18.258 --> 33:20.859
you to take over where he left off.

33:22.900 --> 33:25.897
I'm not the right guy for the job.

33:25.899 --> 33:27.564
Okay? I-I ran away.

33:27.589 --> 33:30.001
I left, you know? Tyler knew that.

33:30.003 --> 33:34.232
Maybe he saw what I see in you now.

33:34.257 --> 33:36.274
That you're brave.

33:36.276 --> 33:37.776
And fearless.

33:38.679 --> 33:41.446
Impossibly resilient.

33:41.448 --> 33:44.449
And you got here all on your own.

33:44.451 --> 33:46.618
No thanks to me.

33:46.620 --> 33:49.120
(chuckles softly)

33:49.957 --> 33:52.123
(sniffles)

34:02.069 --> 34:04.202
(line ringing)

34:04.204 --> 34:05.701
This is Dorian.

34:05.726 --> 34:08.208
This is Detective Sudano,
Grove Hill Police.

34:08.234 --> 34:12.844
You were listed as a contact
person for Georgina Dowling?

34:12.846 --> 34:14.913
Is she okay?

34:19.353 --> 34:22.520
You should come down here.

34:24.958 --> 34:27.359
(keys jangle)

34:45.812 --> 34:48.346
(humming)

34:58.659 --> 35:00.992
(alarm wailing)

35:00.994 --> 35:03.561
(continues humming)

35:13.006 --> 35:15.573
(alarm continues wailing)

35:36.945 --> 35:38.845
Thanks for coming.

35:38.847 --> 35:42.349
I thought we could give
the funeral another shot.

35:43.218 --> 35:45.185
Welcome back.

35:45.484 --> 35:47.417
(chuckles)

35:47.442 --> 35:49.008
♪ ♪

35:56.832 --> 36:00.467
We're here to... honor Tyler.

36:03.605 --> 36:05.438
ALARIC: He was strong.

36:05.440 --> 36:08.169
In the face of so much loss.

36:08.752 --> 36:11.386
ENZO: He fought

36:11.411 --> 36:13.179
the darkness inside himself and won.

36:13.181 --> 36:15.515
I respected the hell out of him.

36:16.885 --> 36:20.587
Tyler was willing to
sacrifice everything for us.

36:21.723 --> 36:24.457
He cared about all of us.

36:24.459 --> 36:27.727
And he was my best friend.

36:31.867 --> 36:35.502
He was so much more than a small-town kid

36:35.504 --> 36:39.539
and he lived so much more
than a small-town life.

36:39.541 --> 36:42.175
I loved him.

36:42.177 --> 36:44.311
You know, we all did.

36:44.313 --> 36:46.646
STEFAN: Look, we don't know

36:46.648 --> 36:49.583
what'll happen next to any of us.

36:49.585 --> 36:53.186
But we can't let that haunt us.

36:53.188 --> 36:57.026
We can't let that make us forget
what we mean to one another.

36:57.051 --> 36:58.884
♪ ♪

37:04.306 --> 37:06.806
A few years ago, I sat on top

37:06.831 --> 37:08.535
of that Ferris wheel with Elena

37:08.537 --> 37:13.640
and I told her how important it
was to appreciate these moments.

37:14.476 --> 37:20.046
Because moments are all we have.

37:25.587 --> 37:27.654
So in honor

37:27.656 --> 37:29.889
of Tyler and Elena,

37:29.891 --> 37:32.892
we need to keep creating
moments like these.

37:35.430 --> 37:38.298
We need to remember to live.

37:38.300 --> 37:40.900
♪ ♪

37:55.060 --> 37:57.094
ALARIC: <i>Dear Elena...</i>

37:57.119 --> 38:00.253
<i>We missed you today.</i>

38:00.255 --> 38:04.496
<i>It was a bad one in a
long series of bad ones.</i>

38:05.360 --> 38:08.595
<i>But you'd like how we came out of it.</i>

38:09.398 --> 38:13.800
<i>I think we made you proud.</i>

38:13.802 --> 38:16.069
(popping)

38:16.071 --> 38:18.638
Wow.

38:18.640 --> 38:21.875
You know, I realized that
I never said thank you.

38:21.877 --> 38:25.159
I'm going to be your wife.

38:25.184 --> 38:27.647
Which means helping you
and protecting you.

38:27.649 --> 38:30.550
Even saving you, if I have to.

38:30.552 --> 38:33.219
Well, hopefully you won't
have to do that anymore.

38:34.923 --> 38:37.657
I remember the last time that
we were at this carnival.

38:37.659 --> 38:40.493
I didn't know how I could possibly deal

38:40.495 --> 38:42.996
with an eternity of being a vampire.

38:42.998 --> 38:46.405
And you told me the only
way to get through it

38:46.430 --> 38:49.369
is to tell yourself that
you're strong enough.

38:49.371 --> 38:51.871
Every day.

38:51.873 --> 38:53.907
Stefan,

38:53.909 --> 38:55.661
you're strong enough.

38:55.686 --> 38:57.586
And if you ever doubt that,

38:57.588 --> 38:59.688
I'm gonna be here to remind you.

38:59.690 --> 39:01.924
♪ ♪

39:14.913 --> 39:17.240
Hey, I was just checking in.

39:17.265 --> 39:18.036
SELINE: Hey.

39:18.061 --> 39:20.943
The girls are doing a little arts
and crafts project before bed.

39:20.945 --> 39:22.845
And I got a little carried away

39:22.847 --> 39:24.629
organizing the garage.

39:24.654 --> 39:26.381
(chuckles) Wow, you're the best.

39:26.383 --> 39:27.883
And thank you for staying late,

39:27.885 --> 39:29.590
and working on your night off.

39:29.615 --> 39:31.920
I... couldn't have got
through today without you.

39:31.922 --> 39:34.256
What can I say? I love your girls.

39:34.258 --> 39:35.924
They keep me feeling young.

39:35.926 --> 39:37.392
I'll be heading home soon.

39:37.394 --> 39:38.794
No rush.

39:45.069 --> 39:46.468
Thank you.

39:46.470 --> 39:48.170
You're a doll.

39:50.341 --> 39:52.541
- You're here.
- Of course I am.

39:52.543 --> 39:54.977
- What happened?
- I saw the truth.

39:54.979 --> 39:57.412
Feelings make you weak.

39:57.414 --> 39:59.848
- I'm done feeling.
- Good.

39:59.850 --> 40:01.917
Now, is your little
existential crisis over?

40:01.919 --> 40:03.552
Because we have things to do.

40:03.554 --> 40:05.921
It'll be fun, I promise.

40:12.096 --> 40:13.462
I'm all yours.

40:13.464 --> 40:14.997
(soft chuckle)

40:20.191 --> 40:22.224
You must be starving.

40:31.982 --> 40:34.616
(man screaming, flesh ripping)

40:41.458 --> 40:44.448
You gonna be mad if I tell you
I'm happy to have you back here?

40:44.473 --> 40:47.496
I just wish it were under
better circumstances.

40:47.498 --> 40:49.131
I'm sorry that I've been M.I.A.

40:49.156 --> 40:51.120
I've just been going through some stuff.

40:51.145 --> 40:53.335
Story of our lives.

40:53.337 --> 40:55.704
So how are the girls?

40:55.706 --> 40:58.674
Practically teenagers.

40:58.676 --> 41:03.078
So I'm guessing you have a photo or two.

41:03.080 --> 41:05.614
Uh, that's them playing
with the puppy filter,

41:05.616 --> 41:07.913
first day of school,

41:07.938 --> 41:10.319
uh, crafting at a
friend's birthday party...

41:10.344 --> 41:11.377
Oh, I love this.

41:11.402 --> 41:13.999
'Line sent it, from from earlier today.

41:14.024 --> 41:16.225
- Seline?
- Mm-hmm.

41:16.227 --> 41:18.126
The nanny.

41:18.128 --> 41:20.996
I know, Ric hired the hot nanny.

41:20.998 --> 41:23.732
No, Caroline, you need to get home now.

41:23.734 --> 41:25.200
♪ ♪

41:25.202 --> 41:27.069
Lizzie?

41:27.071 --> 41:29.204
Hey, Josie?

41:29.206 --> 41:30.995
- Girls?
- Lizzie?

41:31.020 --> 41:33.141
- Girls?
- Josie?

41:33.143 --> 41:35.911
(exasperated sigh) Girls?

41:35.913 --> 41:37.379
Girls!

41:37.381 --> 41:39.581
ALARIC: Girls?

41:43.187 --> 41:45.387
Ric...

